FBIS4-41730 "drsov124_u_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-124 Daily Report 27 Jun 1994 Latvia Citizenship Bill To Be Discussed at European Council Citizenship Bill To Be Discussed at European Council LD2706152694 Riga Radio Riga Network in Russian 1400 GMT 27 Jun 94 LD2706152694 Riga Radio Riga Network Russian BFN [Text] A permanent Latvian delegation today left for the Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe [PACE] to familiarize representatives of PACE with problems related to the process of passing the citizenship bill. A member of the delegation, Aleksandrs Kirsteins, the chairman of the parliamentary group Latvian National Independence Movement, told journalists that these issues would be discussed in political groups of the Council of Europe and PACE commissions, as well as during the course of unofficial meetings with representatives of the EC leadership.
